headline: After Alex Pretti's death in Minneapolis, Trump's strategy of tension comes under scrutiny
description: The American president has tried to persuade public opinion that Democrats and protesters were to blame for the violence caused by his immigration policy. The largest city in Minnesota, where federal agents killed a second person on Saturday, has become his testing ground.

headline: Former French Prime Minister Gabriel Attal pushes ahead with presidential bid, despite doubts within party
French rights ombudsman condemns use of weapons to stop migrants crossing Channel
Russia steps up attacks on Ukraine's shipping routes in the Black Sea
description: Airstrikes on Ukrainian ports have intensified since December 2025. Without a fleet, Kyiv has nevertheless managed to secure grain and container traffic, but the threat of attacks by naval drones is drawing closer.

headline: 'Agreements between the EU and India are a way to show the world there are alternatives to the US'
description: The European Commission president is expected to sign a free trade agreement with India that has been negotiated for years, writes political scientist Christophe Jaffrelot, a specialist on India.

headline: François Kollar shines a light on Parisian workers between the World Wars
description: A former lathe operator at Renault, François Kollar became one of the leading photographers of the industrial world in interwar France. Between 1931 and 1934, he traveled across the country to photograph workers on the job. Several photographs from this series, taken in Paris, have been selected by the Musée Carnavalet for an exhibition dedicated to the capital city's residents.

headline: Valeria Bruni Tedeschi: 'With the rise of the far right, artists feel crushed'
description: In an interview with Le Monde, the actress, who plays the legendary Italian stage performer Eleonora Duse in Pietro Marcello's latest film, discusses the difficult situation facing film d'auteur in Italy.

France is considering banning phones in high schools. This school near Paris already does.
description: The Lycée Michelet, a large school complex with 2,300 students, banned mobile phones in its hallways in April 2025. School officials report positive results from a decision made in agreement with the entire educational community.

headline: US seeks to use Alberta to destabilize Canada
description: The Trump administration and MAGA circles are closely watching the conservative, oil-rich province, particularly as a separatist movement has launched a campaign to organize an independence referendum.

headline: How surveillance companies track smartphone users through advertising data
description: Companies are offering law enforcement agencies the ability to track smartphone users through advertising data gathered on their devices. Le Monde attended confidential presentations of these new surveillance tools to learn more.
